                    </div>
                    <span>This is yet another classical textbook in a Computer Science undergraduate curriculum. It was recommended heartily by my professor (when in fact he has never used it in the course), but I chose not to buy it. And was glad about it aftewards since after reading half of it in the library I found it<p>1) Boring<br>2) Exceedingly and unnecessarily detailed<br>3) Poorly organized<p>For those of you who don't fall asleep while reading the first 200 pages, this might prove to be a good investment. Otherwise, I'd suggest taking good notes during classes and consulting online references, because this book is just not worth the price (in my opinion, of course).</span>
                  
              
